A shorthanded [[Cascading style sheet|CSS]] code for horizontally mirroring elements inside style attribute. Use it inside the <code>style=""</code> attribute of HTML elements like other CSS properties.

*Named Parameter <code>display=</code> allows to change the CSS display property. It defaults to <code>display: inline-block;</code>

When using this template to create the mirrored effect, editors should consider carefully about the [[WP:accessibility|accessibility]].

''{{A note}} This template does not support IE8 or older browsers. IE8 requires cumbersome calculating of matrices. You may implement it into this template if you know how to translate the formula into [[Wikipedia:Lua|Lua]].''

==Examples==
The mirroring happens at the center of the whole object and its effective dimensions will retain the original values of the object as if unmirrored, so you may adjust the position and padding to avoid unwanted overlapping. Use the <code>display=</code> parameter to further control positioning.

